I can answer a couple of them from experience on other engines. On the end
play change, I've had that occur from a burr or other debris on the crank
which rubbed away after running creating the additional end play.

I took my pistons in and had then measured from the pin and two had to be
decked to get the correct height after first marking the piston direction on
one side with a felt pen. I then weighed them and removed material from the
three heavier ones. The cylinders were left alone since they are not part of
the movable drive chain.

I haven't got to lay in the cam to check it yet. If it turns out like some
cams that I have it will probably get sent back with blue dye on the bad
lobes. They hate me for that!

Probably still a month away on getting my aluminum block into a running
engine.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34 PICT-3
71 Trike 1776cc Dual T-4 34 PDSIT-3
VolksAir 1585cc 31 PICT
http://mywebpage.netscape.com/alphahr/case.html
Ray, Kent WA
